elect name=year><option value=2004>2004</option><option value=2005>2005</option><option value=2006 selected>2006</option></select> <input type=submit value=Go></form><p><TABLE WIDTH="94%" BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=0><TR><TD><IMG SRC="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/dateheader_01.gif"></TD><TD WIDTH="100%" background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/dateheader_02.gif"><span CLASS="newsdate">Thu 28 Sep 2006</span></TD><TD><IMG SRC="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/dateheader_03.gif"></TD></TR></TABLE><br><!-------Start News item--><table cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="94%" border=0>             <tr>           <td width=23><img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_01.jpg"></td>           <td  width=100%        background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_02.jpg"></td>           <td><img         src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_03.jpg"></td></tr>         <tr>           <td           background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_04.jpg" width="17px">&nbsp;</td>           <td             background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_05.jpg"><a name="21612"></a><span CLASS="newstitle">More Screens for Serpent's Spine</span><br><span class="feat"><a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/forums/b1/99209241">[Post A Comment]</a> - <a href=pagetools/pagetools.php?act=printnews&id=21612>Print News</a> | <a href="?dir=pagetools&content=mailnews&id=21612">Mail News</a></span><br>RPGVault has published six new exclusive <a href="http://rpgvault.ign.com/articles/736/736028p1.html">screenshots</a> from the Serpent's Spine expansion.  From all reports, players are enjoying this new expansion and all the incredible new zones it brought to the game.<br><br><span CLASS="newsby">-- <a href="/siteinfo/mail.php?staff=Kwill">Kwill</a> @ Thu 28 Sep 2006</span><br><br><br><img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/spacer.gif" width="540px" height=1></td>           <td           background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_06.jpg" width="17px">&nbsp;</td></tr>         <tr>           <td width=23><img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_07.jpg"></td>           <td           background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_08.jpg"></td>           <td><img         src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_09.jpg"></td></tr></table></p><!-------End News item--><p><TABLE WIDTH="94%" BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=0><TR><TD><IMG SRC="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/dateheader_01.gif"></TD><TD WIDTH="100%" background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/dateheader_02.gif"><span CLASS="newsdate">Wed 27 Sep 2006</span></TD><TD><IMG SRC="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/dateheader_03.gif"></TD></TR></TABLE><br><!-------Start News item--><table cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="94%" border=0>             <tr>           <td width=23><img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_01.jpg"></td>           <td  width=100%        background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_02.jpg"></td>           <td><img         src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_03.jpg"></td></tr>         <tr>           <td           background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_04.jpg" width="17px">&nbsp;</td>           <td             background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_05.jpg"><a name="21532"></a><span CLASS="newstitle">Serpent's Spine Maps</span><br><span class="feat"><a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/forums/b1/99181718">[Post A Comment]</a> - <a href=pagetools/pagetools.php?act=printnews&id=21532>Print News</a> | <a href="?dir=pagetools&content=mailnews&id=21532">Mail News</a></span><br>Need maps for the Serpent's Spine zones?  They are all posted on <a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&message.id=282525">EQPlayers</a> and can be downloaded from the link to the Raging Fury guild's website on the thread.<br><br><span CLASS="newsby">-- <a href="/siteinfo/mail.php?staff=Kwill">Kwill</a> @ Wed 27 Sep 2006</span><br><br><br><a name="21531"></a><span CLASS="newstitle">September 27 Patch Message</span><br><span class="feat"><a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/forums/b1/99181634">[Post A Comment]</a> - <a href=pagetools/pagetools.php?act=printnews&id=21531>Print News</a> | <a href="?dir=pagetools&content=mailnews&id=21531">Mail News</a></span><br>September 27th, 2006<br>_____________________<br><br>*** NPCs ***<br>- Moved Ezna Connoy and Tavin of the Wild a little further south. While they are one with the animals around them, some of their customers were unhappy with their location.<br>- Increased the elemental essence drop rates off the four elemental gods in Planes of Power. <br>- Frannie in Surefall Glade now carries shiny new combine smithy hammers.<br>- Removed Spin Stun from the NPCs in Infected Paw.<br>- Improved run animations for both male and female Drakkin<br><br>*** Tradeskills ***<br>- Altered the systematic spell research spells Belt of Magi'Kot and Girdle of Magi'Kot to better match the systematic system.<br>- Added the spells Summon Glowing Bauble, Summon Platinum Choker, Summon Runed Mantle, Summon Sapphire Bracelet, Summon Spiked Ring, Summon Steel Bracelet, Summon Jewelry Bag to the systematic spell research system.<br>- Vergalid Clay, Medicinal Moss, and Vergalid Slave Manacles have all moved to Sunderock outside of Vergalid.<br><br>*** Spells ***<br>- Four of the mage summoned spells in Serpent’s Spine are now tradable.<br>- Damage from Necromancer and Shadowknight lich-type spells has been reduced by a third.<br>- The range on Mayong and Ayonae bane clicky items has been decreased.<br>- Several unresistable melee attacks no longer work on other players.<br>- Corrected a problem that was causing some spells to resist more often than they should.<br>- Bolt spells should now behave more consistently.<br>- Fixed a problem with illusion spells making everyone default to the same appearance.<br>- Invisibility should no longer stack with other forms.<br><br>*** Missions ***<br>- Several issues with the Finding Fibblebrap mission have been fixed.<br><br>*** Items ***<br>- The appearance of evergreen leaves on the ground has changed. They now look more leaf like!<br><br>*** AAs ***<br>- Corrected the level requirements for Greater Blood Tithe and Funeral Dirge.<br>- Players should now be able to get AA experience from Monster Missions.<br><br>*** UI ***<br>- Players using custom UIs should now be able to go back to character select from in game and see their characters.<br> <br> <br>- The EverQuest Team <br><br><br><span CLASS="newsby">-- <a href="/siteinfo/mail.php?staff=Kwill">Kwill</a> @ Wed 27 Sep 2006</span><br><br><br><img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/spacer.gif" width="540px" height=1></td>           <td           background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_06.jpg" width="17px">&nbsp;</td></tr>         <tr>           <td width=23><img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_07.jpg"></td>           <td           background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_08.jpg"></td>           <td><img         src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_09.jpg"></td></tr></table></p><!-------End News item--><p><TABLE WIDTH="94%" BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=0><TR><TD><IMG SRC="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/dateheader_01.gif"></TD><TD WIDTH="100%" background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/dateheader_02.gif"><span CLASS="newsdate">Tue 26 Sep 2006</span></TD><TD><IMG SRC="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/dateheader_03.gif"></TD></TR></TABLE><br><!-------Start News item--><table cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="94%" border=0>             <tr>           <td width=23><img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_01.jpg"></td>           <td  width=100%        background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_02.jpg"></td>           <td><img         src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_03.jpg"></td></tr>         <tr>           <td           background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_04.jpg" width="17px">&nbsp;</td>           <td             background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_05.jpg"><a name="21501"></a><span CLASS="newstitle">Smed's Blog: Digitial Distribution</span><br><span class="feat"><a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/forums/b1/99165549">[Post A Comment]</a> - <a href=pagetools/pagetools.php?act=printnews&id=21501>Print News</a> | <a href="?dir=pagetools&content=mailnews&id=21501">Mail News</a></span><br>I mananged to miss John Smedley's latest blog when it came out on September 12, but it's still relevant for the recent release of the Serpent's Spine expansion.  Why is Serpent's Spine only using digital distribution?  Is it because EQ is not marketing itself anymore, and fading away? Nope.  It's because the President of SOE has decided that digital distribution is the medium of the future, and he's willing to bet $1000 that he's right.<br><br>Read his latest blog, <a href="http://stationblog.wordpress.com/">Dear Michael Patcher,</a> below.<p><a href="fullstory.php?id=21501">Read More...</a><br><br><span CLASS="newsby">-- <a href="/siteinfo/mail.php?staff=Kwill">Kwill</a> @ Tue 26 Sep 2006</span><br><br><br><img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/spacer.gif" width="540px" height=1></td>           <td           background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_06.jpg" width="17px">&nbsp;</td></tr>         <tr>           <td width=23><img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_07.jpg"></td>           <td           background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_08.jpg"></td>           <td><img         src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_09.jpg"></td></tr></table></p><!-------End News item--><p><TABLE WIDTH="94%" BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=0><TR><TD><IMG SRC="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/dateheader_01.gif"></TD><TD WIDTH="100%" background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/dateheader_02.gif"><span CLASS="newsdate">Mon 25 Sep 2006</span></TD><TD><IMG SRC="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/dateheader_03.gif"></TD></TR></TABLE><br><!-------Start News item--><table cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="94%" border=0>             <tr>           <td width=23><img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_01.jpg"></td>           <td  width=100%        background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_02.jpg"></td>           <td><img         src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_03.jpg"></td></tr>         <tr>           <td           background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_04.jpg" width="17px">&nbsp;</td>           <td             background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_05.jpg"><a name="21467"></a><span CLASS="newstitle">Male and Female Players in EverQuest</span><br><span class="feat"><a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/forums/b1/99148271">[Post A Comment]</a> - <a href=pagetools/pagetools.php?act=printnews&id=21467>Print News</a> | <a href="?dir=pagetools&content=mailnews&id=21467">Mail News</a></span><br>There are some significant differences in why gals and guys play EverQuest, according to Nick Yee's article, <a href="http://www.nickyee.com/eqt/menwomen.html">Men are from Ogguk. Women are from Kelethin</a>.  It may surprise you with what some of his research has uncovered! How about, women get more satisfaction out of killing a mob?  For those interested in the social aspects of EQ, his article is a good read, and it may help you understand your fellow players a little better.<br><br>Nick Yee is one of the first and probably the most widely cited of any EverQuest researcher out there.  Some of you may have participated in his research.  There's lots more on his website, <a href="http://www.nickyee.com/eqt/home.html">The Norrathian Scrolls.</a>  Check it out!<br><br><span CLASS="newsby">-- <a href="/siteinfo/mail.php?staff=Kwill">Kwill</a> @ Mon 25 Sep 2006</span><br><br><br><a name="21466"></a><span CLASS="newstitle">Expansion Features</span><br><span class="feat"><a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/forums/b1/99147705">[Post A Comment]</a> - <a href=pagetools/pagetools.php?act=printnews&id=21466>Print News</a> | <a href="?dir=pagetools&content=mailnews&id=21466">Mail News</a></span><br>Here's a handy list of all the <a href="http://eqvault.ign.com/static.php?page=expansions">EverQuest expansions</a> ever released and what came into the game with each one.<br><br>Wondering what expansions you need? This will give you some idea of the features you will get with each one.<br><br>It's also just interesting to see how the game has evolved over time.<br><br><span CLASS="newsby">-- <a href="/siteinfo/mail.php?staff=Kwill">Kwill</a> @ Mon 25 Sep 2006</span><br><br><br><img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/spacer.gif" width="540px" height=1></td>           <td           background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_06.jpg" width="17px">&nbsp;</td></tr>         <tr>           <td width=23><img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_07.jpg"></td>           <td           background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_08.jpg"></td>           <td><img         src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_09.jpg"></td></tr></table></p><!-------End News item--><p><TABLE WIDTH="94%" BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=0><TR><TD><IMG SRC="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/dateheader_01.gif"></TD><TD WIDTH="100%" background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/dateheader_02.gif"><span CLASS="newsdate">Sat 23 Sep 2006</span></TD><TD><IMG SRC="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/dateheader_03.gif"></TD></TR></TABLE><br><!-------Start News item--><table cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="94%" border=0>             <tr>           <td width=23><img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_01.jpg"></td>           <td  width=100%        background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_02.jpg"></td>           <td><img         src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_03.jpg"></td></tr>         <tr>           <td           background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_04.jpg" width="17px">&nbsp;</td>           <td             background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_05.jpg"><a name="21417"></a><span CLASS="newstitle">Weekly Screenshot</span><br><span class="feat"><a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/forums/b1/99121179">[Post A Comment]</a> - <a href=pagetools/pagetools.php?act=printnews&id=21417>Print News</a> | <a href="?dir=pagetools&content=mailnews&id=21417">Mail News</a></span><br>Hive castle entrance in Stone Hive zone from the Serpent's Spine expansion.<br><!-- Step 1 - create a link to the real image.  Do NOT close the link --><br><A HREF="http://eqvault.ign.com/screenshots/image.php?ss=675"><br><!-- Step 2 - put a link to the thumbnail image next, before closing the link --><img src="http://eqvault.ign.com/screenshots/thumb.php?ss=675"><!-- Step 3 - Now - just close the link --><br></A><br><br><span CLASS="newsby">-- <a href="/siteinfo/mail.php?staff=Kwill">Kwill</a> @ Sat 23 Sep 2006</span><br><br><br><a name="21413"></a><span CLASS="newstitle">No Armor Dye for Drakkins</span><br><span class="feat"><a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/forums/b1/99116843">[Post A Comment]</a> - <a href=pagetools/pagetools.php?act=printnews&id=21413>Print News</a> | <a href="?dir=pagetools&content=mailnews&id=21413">Mail News</a></span><br>Seems like a lot of Drakkin race players have an issue with not being able to dye their armor, but that's the way they are designed, unless they use an illusion to change their racial graphics, in which case the armor dye does appear.  Kytherea <a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&message.id=288580">clarifies:</a><br><br>"We wanted to let you know that it is intentional that Drakkin can not dye any of the armor they wear, whether it is armors from previous expansions or new armor, wearable by all or by Drakkin only.  The dye will technically take but will not appear if the character is in Drakkin form.  If a Drakkin uses an illusion to change racial graphics, the dyed armor will show as it was dyed. "<br><br>And why can't you dye Drakkin armor?  The loss of armor detail, Kyth explains:<br><br>"There may be some lore reason behind [not being able to dye Drakkin armor] but I think mainly it is because we have the ability now to offer a greater variety of skins for armor making armor sets more unique looking.  Dying armor takes away some of the detail of the armor.<br><br>I was assured though that armor sets that are not coordinating will be rectified.  So if, for instance, you find a set that is mainly black with silver bracers and silver boots but one bracer shows up green, it will be fixed so it is coordinating as it should."<br><br>So at least you won't have to be a fashion disaster!<br><br><span CLASS="newsby">-- <a href="/siteinfo/mail.php?staff=Kwill">Kwill</a> @ Sat 23 Sep 2006</span><br><br><br><a name="21412"></a><span CLASS="newstitle">New Con Levels and Downtime in Raid Zones</span><br><span class="feat"><a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/forums/b1/99116758">[Post A Comment]</a> - <a href=pagetools/pagetools.php?act=printnews&id=21412>Print News</a> | <a href="?dir=pagetools&content=mailnews&id=21412">Mail News</a></span><br>An EQ player posted on the <a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&message.id=291464">SOE forums</a> that "I went into the plane of hate today with my 66 druid to grab some quest pieces and noticed that in this zone, my cooldown timer is 5 minutes.<br><br>I conned a rat (light blue con) and surely enough, it says "It would take an army to defeat this creature".<br><br>This hardly seems right considering I can root rot it to death with minimal effort... Would it be possible to modify the "raid mob" code to not include mobs that are essentially trivial?  Maybe put in a level check for > 10 level difference?<br><br>Developer Nodyin replied: "The con message is intended to indicate the challenge level for those players for whom the content is tuned. That means that if an NPC is a raid NPC for level 50 players but can be soloed by a level 75 it will still be considered a Raid npc and give a 5 minute cooldown. Basepop in a raid zone such as PoHate, Deathknell or Ashengate will also give the 5 minute timer.<br><br>Part of the reasoning for this is that sometimes you'll be suprised when you attack a blue con npc and find it's much harder than the con color would indiate. Now with the new con message you'll understand why that blue con is so challenging - it's an event mob not a normal blue con."<br><br> <br> <br><br><br><span CLASS="newsby">-- <a href="/siteinfo/mail.php?staff=Kwill">Kwill</a> @ Sat 23 Sep 2006</span><br><br><br><a name="21411"></a><span CLASS="newstitle">Fourth Podcast from SOE</span><br><span class="feat"><a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/forums/b1/99116734">[Post A Comment]</a> - <a href=pagetools/pagetools.php?act=printnews&id=21411>Print News</a> | <a href="?dir=pagetools&content=mailnews&id=21411">Mail News</a></span><br>SOE Posts:<br><br>Offical SOE Podcast Number 4! <br><br>We are proud to offer the fourth official SOE podcast to our communities, and hope you all enjoy the latest installment of our podcast series. As always the two fun loving hosts for the show are Brenlo and Blackguard. This podcast covers everything from EQII to EQOA to Planetside, so be sure to tune in for Blackguard's final Podcast. <br><br>You can <a href="http://eqplayers.station.sony.com/news_article.vm?id=50237">download</a> the MP3 file directly or subscribe to the RSS feed by clicking the button. We have both high and low bandwidth versions of the podcast available.<br><br> <br><br><br><span CLASS="newsby">-- <a href="/siteinfo/mail.php?staff=Kwill">Kwill</a> @ Sat 23 Sep 2006</span><br><br><br><img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/spacer.gif" width="540px" height=1></td>           <td           background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_06.jpg" width="17px">&nbsp;</td></tr>         <tr>           <td width=23><img src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_07.jpg"></td>           <td           background="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_08.jpg"></td>           <td><img         src="http://vnmedia.ign.com/eqvault.ign.com/skins/default/newsbox_09.jpg"></td></tr></table></p><!-------End News item--></center>
</td></tr></table></DIV>
